    <!-- Platform Description by AI -->
    <section class="doc-section">
      <h2>1. Platform Description</h2>
      <p>
        <span class="glow-term">SurgiVision VR</span> is a state-of-the-art virtual reality platform that represents a paradigm shift in medical and anatomical education. By leveraging modern real-time WebGL engine configurations, modular C# physics bindings within Unity 3D, and the Unity XR Interaction Toolkit, the platform addresses the crucial limitations of classical laboratory anatomy learning—such as the high acquisition costs of cadavers and physical simulators.
      </p>
      <p>
        The platform’s architectural core is split into three core modules: the <strong>Human Anatomy Exploration Module</strong>, the <strong>Interactive Organ Study Deck</strong>, and the <strong>Surgical Procedure Sandbox</strong>. It is uniquely engineered to serve both modern Western medical students (MBBS, BDS, Nursing) and traditional Indian medicine scholars (Ayurveda BAMS). It maps complex clinical anatomical structures directly to classical concepts of <span class="highlight-span">Marma Points</span> (vital nodes), <span class="highlight-span">Dhatus</span> (tissue layers), and <span class="highlight-span">Srotas</span> (physiological pathways) referencing texts like the Sushruta Samhita.
      </p>
      
      <h3>Core Learning Workflows:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Anatomy Visualization:</strong> Multi-tiered layer controls allow volumetric isolation of the skeletal, muscular, nervous, cardiovascular, respiratory, and digestive networks.</li>
        <li><strong>Organ Correlation:</strong> Side-by-side tabs offer comparative analyses between classical physiology descriptions and contemporary micro-anatomy structures.</li>
        <li><strong>Surgical Training:</strong> Real-time coordinate checking guides students through procedural milestones (such as incision angles, tissue retraction, and ligating vessels) with automated score deduction for deviations.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Project Architecture Details -->
    <section class="doc-section">
      <h2>2. Project Architecture & Technical Stack</h2>
      <p>
        The deployment ecosystem is built on a scalable, modular framework utilizing <strong>Unity 3D</strong> as the rendering core and **C#** for spatial manipulation, tool handling, and evaluation logic.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>User Interface Layer:</strong> Responsive, high-fidelity layouts styled with premium vanilla CSS tokens, featuring hover followers, card glassmorphism, and responsive timelines.</li>
        <li><strong>3D Mesh Formats:</strong> Optimized FBX and OBJ assets imported from Blender, maintaining low polygon counts for mobile-XR rendering targets.</li>
        <li><strong>XR Interaction Engine:</strong> Configured using the Unity XR Interaction Toolkit, enabling natural controller mappings for Grab, Point, Rotate, and Select options.</li>
        <li><strong>Database Integration:</strong> SQLite for secure local student profile progress, lesson completion marks, and assessment scores, with cloud sync modules via Firebase.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

